# ADA Accessibility Auditor Spec

## Overview
AI-powered accessibility auditing tool that analyzes web pages for WCAG compliance and provides actionable recommendations.

## Requirements

### Core Features
- URL input for web page analysis
- AI-powered accessibility audit
- WCAG 2.1 compliance checking
- Issue categorization by severity
- Detailed recommendations
- Code examples for fixes
- Export audit reports

### Audit Categories
- **Critical**: Issues that prevent access
- **Serious**: Major barriers to accessibility
- **Moderate**: Significant usability issues
- **Minor**: Small improvements needed

### Analysis Areas
- Semantic HTML structure
- ARIA attributes and roles
- Keyboard navigation
- Color contrast
- Alt text for images
- Form labels and validation
- Focus management
- Screen reader compatibility
- Heading hierarchy
- Link text clarity

### Report Features
- Overall accessibility score
- Issue count by severity
- Detailed issue descriptions
- Code snippets showing problems
- Recommended fixes with examples
- WCAG guideline references
- Priority ranking

## Technical Implementation

### API Integration
```javascript
POST /api/audit-accessibility
Body: { url: string }
Response: {
  score: number,
  issues: Array<{
    severity: string,
    category: string,
    description: string,
    element: string,
    recommendation: string,
    wcagReference: string
  }>
}
```

### Issue Structure
```javascript
{
  id: string,
  severity: 'Critical' | 'Serious' | 'Moderate' | 'Minor',
  category: string,
  title: string,
  description: string,
  element: string,
  currentCode: string,
  recommendedCode: string,
  wcagGuideline: string,
  impact: string
}
```

### UI Components
- URL input with validation
- Audit button with loading state
- Score display with visual indicator
- Issue cards grouped by severity
- Expandable issue details
- Code comparison viewer
- Export button (PDF, JSON)

## User Flow
1. User enters website URL
2. Clicks "Run Audit"
3. AI analyzes page for accessibility issues
4. Results displayed with score and issues
5. User reviews issues by severity
6. Clicks on issue to see details and fixes
7. Exports report for documentation

## Audit Process
1. Fetch page HTML
2. Parse DOM structure
3. Check WCAG 2.1 guidelines
4. Identify violations
5. Generate recommendations
6. Calculate accessibility score
7. Format report

## Success Criteria
- Complete audit in under 10 seconds
- Identify 95%+ of common accessibility issues
- Provide actionable recommendations
- Clear code examples for all issues
- Accurate WCAG guideline references
- Score calculation matches manual audit
